    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ANGLO AMERICAN PROFIT IS UP</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Increased prices for platinum and growing demand for diamonds buoy Anglo American's first-half profit up 77 percent to $951 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Buoyed by increased platinum prices and growing demand for diamonds, Anglo American P.L.C., the world's largest mining company, said its first-half profit rose 77 percent to $951 million. The increase outstripped analysts' forecasts and the performance of its rivals Billiton and Rio Tinto, both based in Britain. Analysts attributed the demand for Anglo's mining products and for the diamonds mined by De Beers, in which Anglo holds about one-third of the stock, to the booming United States economy.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
